**Per-frame vs Simulation Tick distinction**: In game loops, some systems must run every frame (e.g., `movementSystem` for smooth interpolation at variable framerate) while others run at fixed simulation intervals (economy, combat, AI). The orchestrator handles the latter — all 48 systems at a 1.0s interval. `movementSystem(delta, speed)` stays per-frame because jerky movement would be visible to the player at 1 FPS tick rate.
