`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
**Koota ECS bridge pattern**: The external modification added `syncBeforeFrame()` / `syncAfterFrame()` calls wrapping the game loop body. This is a standard pattern when migrating ECS systems — the bridge syncs entity state between the old ECS (Miniplex) and new ECS (Koota) each frame, ensuring both systems see consistent data. `invalidateSnapshot()` after `orchestratorTick()` ensures React subscribers re-render after game state changes.
