`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
**Why this matters architecturally**: Before US-003, GameLoop was a "god function" that knew about every system individually. Now it only knows about two things: (1) `movementSystem` for per-frame interpolation, and (2) `orchestratorTick()` for everything else. This decouples the rendering frame loop from game logic ordering — you can add/remove/reorder systems in `registerSystems.ts` without touching the rendering component. The orchestrator also enables profiling per-phase and toggling systems at runtime via `setSystemEnabled()`.
